3 lactation educator] to a pregnant or postpartum individual from conception
4 through one year postpartum.
5 “(2)(a) The Oregon Health Authority shall establish a community-based
6 perinatal services access program to support activities that increase access
7 to culturally specific and culturally competent community-based services
8 during the perinatal period. The program must issue grants or contracts to
9 eligible entities with a demonstrated ability to offer the activities described
10 in this subsection, including culturally specific organizations, the nine
11 federally recognized Indian tribes in this state, nonprofit organizations and
12 businesses.
13 “(b) Grants and contracts issued under this section may be used for
14 purposes including, but not limited to:
15 “(A) Paying for costs of required training and education to provide
16 community-based services during the perinatal period, including tuition, fees,
17 books and other materials and supplies;
18 “(B) Providing wages and financial benefits for individuals who are
19 training to provide community-based services during the perinatal period;
20 “(C) Outreach and recruitment to attract individuals to training programs
21 to provide community-based services during the perinatal period;
22 “(D) Funding for culturally specific or community-based organizations
23 and programs to:
24 “(i) Establish or expand community-based services during the perinatal
25 period;
26 “(ii) Support billing insurance for community-based services during the
27 perinatal period;
28 “(iii) Provide training and mentoring for providers of community-based
29 services during the perinatal period; and
30 “(iv) Conduct consumer or provider education and research regarding
