SB 1568-A3 2/20/26
Proposed Amendments to A-Eng. SB 1568 Page 15

1 consultation.
2 “(2) ‘Lactation consultation’ means the clinical application of scientific
3 principles and evidence to provide care related to lactation to childbearing
4 families. Lactation consultation includes, but is not limited to:
5 “(a) Client assessment through systematic collection of data;
6 “(b) Data analysis;
7 “(c) Creation of a care plan;
8 “(d) Implementation of the care plan, including demonstration and in-
9 structions to clients and communication with the clients’ primary care pro-
10 vider;
11 “(e) Evaluation of client outcomes;
12 “(f) Problem identification and treatment;
13 “(g) Recommendation and use of assistive devices; and
14 “(h) Lactation education to childbearing families and to health care pro-
15 viders.
16 “[(3) ‘Lactation counselor’ means a person certified by the Academy of
17 Lactation Policy and Practice, or its successor organization, as approved by
18 the Health Licensing Office by rule, as a clinical lactation care provider who
19 has demonstrated the necessary skills, knowledge and attitude to provide clin-
20 ical support to families that are thinking, or have questions, about
21 breastfeeding or that have problems with breastfeeding.]
22 “[(4) ‘Lactation educator’ means a person certified by the Childbirth and
23 Postpartum Professional Association, or its successor organization, as ap-
24 proved by the office by rule, as a certified lactation educator to educate, counsel
25 and support families by providing evidence-based information about lactation
26 and breastfeeding.]
