10 the operative date specified in section 25 of this 2026 Act.
11 “SECTION 25. (1) Sections 9, 11 and 17 of this 2026 Act and the
12 amendments to ORS 414.668, 676.380, 676.386 and 743A.081 by sections
13 5, 13, 19a and 20a of this 2026 Act become operative on January 1, 2028.
14 “(2) The Oregon Health Authority, the Department of Consumer
15 and Business Services, a coordinated care organization and an insurer
16 may take any action before the operative date specified in subsection
17 (1) of this section that is necessary to enable those entities to exercise,
18 on and after the operative date specified in subsection (1) of this sec-
19 tion, all of the duties, functions and powers conferred on those entities
20 by sections 9, 11 and 17 of this 2026 Act and the amendments to ORS
21 414.668, 676.380, 676.386 and 743A.081 by sections 5, 13, 19a and 20a of this
22 2026 Act.
23 “SECTION 26. This 2026 Act being necessary for the immediate
24 preservation of the public peace, health and safety, an emergency is
25 declared to exist, and this 2026 Act takes effect on its passage.”.
